463
0:18:30.26,000 --> 0:18:33,000
(Applause)

464
0:18:33.26,000 --> 0:18:36,000
A couple months went by,

465
0:18:36.26,000 --> 0:18:38,000
and I had just forgotten all about it.

466
0:18:38.26,000 --> 0:18:4,000
And I finally decided,

467
0:18:40.26,000 --> 0:18:42,000
oh gosh, I've got to go to the court and do this crazy case.

468
0:18:42.26,000 --> 0:18:44,000
And I got into my car

469
0:18:44.26,000 --> 0:18:46,000
and I was feeling really overwhelmed -- overwhelmed.

470
0:18:46.26,000 --> 0:18:48,000
And I got in my car and I went to this courthouse.

471
0:18:48.26,000 --> 0:18:51,000
And I was thinking, this is going to be so difficult, so painful.

472
0:18:51.26,000 --> 0:18:54,000
And I finally got out of the car and I started walking up to the courthouse.

473
0:18:54.26,000 --> 0:18:56,000
And as I was walking up the steps of this courthouse,

474
0:18:56.26,000 --> 0:18:59,000
there was an older black man who was the janitor in this courthouse.

475
0:18:59.26,000 --> 0:19:01,000
When this man saw me, he came over to me

476
0:19:01.26,000 --> 0:19:03,000
and he said, "Who are you?"

477
0:19:03.26,000 --> 0:19:06,000
I said, "I'm a lawyer." He said, "You're a lawyer?" I said, "Yes, sir."

478
0:19:06.26,000 --> 0:19:08,000
And this man came over to me

479
0:19:08.26,000 --> 0:19:1,000
and he hugged me.

480
0:19:10.26,000 --> 0:19:12,000
And he whispered in my ear.

481
0:19:12.26,000 --> 0:19:14,000
